Set Up First-Party Data for Segment Intelligence

Gain insights on your data by connecting your first-party data to segment Intelligence. All steps in this section are mandatory and must be completed for a successful installation.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience	Available in: Enterprise and Unlimited Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To manage Data Cloud:	Data Cloud Admin permission set
To set up first party data in Segment Intelligence:	Data Cloud Admin permission set
Step 1. Set Up the Marketing Cloud Engagement Data Kit

You can create data stream bundles with the engagement data kit in Marketing Cloud Engagement to pull engagement data into Segment Intelligence.

Set up a Marketing Cloud connection in Data Cloud.
Create a Marketing Cloud starter bundle in Data Cloud.
When creating the bundle, select the Email Studio data bundle.
Step 2. Set Up the Commerce Cloud Revenue Kit
Use the Commerce Cloud Data Kit to pull Commerce data into Segment Intelligence. See Create a B2C Commerce Data Kit.
Step 3. Select the Commerce Cloud Revenue Metric
On the Segment Intelligence setup page, under First-Party Data Prerequisites, click Select Revenue Metric.
From the dropdown list, select the revenue metric’s data model object.
Select the metric you want to use for revenue.
Save your changes.
